selves war correspondents, claim all the rights of soldiers and refuse to accept any of the responsibilities. They all suffer from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 diarrhoea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
 of the tongue and constipation of the ego." (Officer, P.R.O.).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 "There are twelve jeeps and around 30 correspondents. Each correspondent wants a jeep. The agency men won't ride with any other agency man and the specials won't ride with other spe
cials, and the still photographers.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 Won\rquote t ride with other still photographers. " (Officer, P.R.O.).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 4. GENERAL MORALE}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 There is no particular change in general morale. Mentions are about average (56%) and a very large percentage of these (99%) c
ontinue to be favorable. The more specific morale situation also continues without noteworthy change. As before, the only particularly bad morale factors are mail service and (among officers) dislike of superiors and disappointment in promotions. In both 
cases some improvement over last week is indicated. Confidence in an early victory continues to be reflected in letters and references to an early expected return to the U. S. are rather numerous. Quotations:
\par 
\par "Ours is really a great outfit and I am proud to be with it." (1st Bn., 18th Inf.).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 "We had a very successful day on the 5th and have been complimented highly all down the line. I'm very proud and for once could tell them I was completely satisfied
. I don't think your ancestors will like us one bit." (99 B.G. (H.)), to a girl with Italian name).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 "The machine gunners of the bomber crews we've worked with have done a marvelous job and we have a lot of respect for their ability." (81 Ftr.. Gr., 93 Ftr. Sq.).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086910 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
"I suppose you think that we are fighting a helluva war talking about shows and (lances, but this kind of work gets monotous once in a while and it's not all pie and honey either. Although we can't complain a bit." (205 M.P. Co.).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 "I still don't know what this war is about but I do know she is a rough game if it\rquote s for fun." (95 Sq., 82 Gr.).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 "Honey, after I get back, I'm going to try my damn best to forget everything that ever happened over here and just concentrate on our happiness. I w
ouldn't relive this for a hundred million dollars." (48 Surg. Mosp.).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 "I swear that if and when any more (Censor: promotions) are handed out and I am not the first to get the next one, they will never get any work out of me again--I have had enough of 
this damn outfit and everyone connected with it." (97 B.G., 340 B. Sq.).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 "Brother I'm tired, homesick, scared and disgusted. I withdrew my application for a regular commission." (414 B.S., 97 B.G.).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6436052 5. FOREIGN LANGUAGE}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086910 
